experiment.comment: Reactive volume-time profiles were obtained through personal communication with the authors. The volumes are normalized values. Simulations should be carried out using the constant U-V reactor model.

The authors determined the IDTs experimentally based on both the pressure profiles and the OH* profiles. They found that the two experimental results were quasi-identical, i.e., the differences were negligible. In the XML, the IDTs are defined based on the OH* profiles because it was found that numerically it gives much more stable results if a volume-time (or pressure-time) profile is considered due to the typically noisy nature of these profiles.
